        "committer": {
          "name": "Serguei Smirnov",
          "email": "ssmirnov@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2021-01-29 22:11:49.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-14386 lnet: backport fix for remote MR peer ni selection",
        "message": "LU-14386 lnet: backport fix for remote MR peer ni selection\n\nThis is a partial back-port of LU-12053 from MRR series:\nAn MR peer can have multiple interfaces some of which we might\nhave a route to. The primary NID of the peer might not necessarily\nspecify a NID we have a route to. When looking up a route, we must\niterate over all the nets the peer is on and select the one which\nwe can route to. Taking into consideration the peer can exist on\nmultiple routed networks we also have a simple round robin algorithm\nto iterate over all the networks we can reach the peer on.\n\nLustre-change: https://review.whamcloud.com/34625\nLustre-commit: 52eef817974304d0107caaec023a2ed341c164e0\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=lnet-selftest,sanity-lnet\nSigned-off-by: Serguei Smirnov <ssmirnov@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I04e47ef24ae6fe41b8c1d97f9cf4e2830754e215\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_12"
    }
  },
